   * Contracts
          How to obtain information about contracts with NHTSA.

   * Discretionary Federal Assistance

   * DOT Waivers
          The President's Executive Memorandum of April 21, 1998,
          encourages the granting of waivers to streamline internal
          processes and procedures. Secretary Slater, as reflected in his
          Policy Statement, fully endorses the use of waivers on a
          Departmentwide scale. This site provides a comprehensive look at
          DOT's implementation of this important initiative.

   * FOIA
          Information about the Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) and
          NHTSA including how to make a FOIA request.

   * NHTSA SBIR Program
          The 1999 NHTSA Small Business Innovation Research (SBIR) program
          topics have just been released as part of the DOT solicitation.

   * Transportation Equity Act for the 21st Century

   * NHTSA and the Federal Register
          NHTSA items in the Federal Register and a link to the Federal
          Register

   * Welcome to the Deaf Employees Association for the United States
          Department of Transportation.


